article.headline: Evansville 69, Drake 68
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Kyle Anslinger scored a career high 29 points, including 9-of-10 from 3-point range, and Evansville beat Drake 69-68 Saturday to snap a 21-game road losing streak. Anslinger, who closed out the game by making five straight threes, hit the most 3-pointers in a Missouri Valley Conference game since Creighton's Kyle Korver had nine against Evansville on Jan. 13, 2003. Evansville (7-16, 3-12 MVC) blew an 11-point lead, but Anslinger's final 3-pointer, along with a 3-point play by Matt Webster in the final minute, preserved the win. Drake's last four home losses have been by a total of nine points. Chris Bryant, who led the Bulldogs (12-14, 5-10) with 15 points, missed a 35-footer at the buzzer. Down 11 with 7:22 left, Drake went on a 12-2 run and got as close as 60-59. Chaun Brooks added 11 for the Bulldogs. Webster scored 18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for the Purple Aces.
